body.name: 3U Server Chassis - Compact 12" Deep 19" Rackmount ATX Computer Case (Back or Front Rack Mount for Easy Access to Rear Components & Ports) 4 Bay 1x5.25 3x3.5; 4X Full Expansion Slots -Tupavco TP1833
features: [Versatile] 3-Way Setup by hinges attach position - (1) Front - Panel access (2) Side - Wall Mount (3) Back - for easy access to Rear I/O Components and Ports
[Ultra Compact] With a depth of only 11.8 inches TP1833 is perfect if you are low on space but want full-size case benefits.

[Compatible] Rack Mount Enclosure supports all types of ATX motherboards (full-size ATX, microATX, miniATX) as well as the standard ATX power supply (NOT INCLUDED). Compatible with any standard 19" Rack Cabinet

[Ports & Connections] Support for 4 Bays, 1 x 5.25", 3 x 3.5, 4 (full height) expansion slots, up to 7 x 60mm fans (2 included), PS-2 ATX Power Supply (NOT INCLUDED); Front: Power and reset switch, 2 x USB 2.0, Power and 2x HDD LED
[Reliable] Constructed of a Heavy-Duty & Rugged Steel (1.0 mm) and Aluminum (for handles) with industrial quality and ruggedness. No Assembly Required

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: TP1833 3U Server Rack Mount Chassis If you are in need of a full-size server chassis but lack the space needed, you should consider the TP1833 server chassis as the best choice. The 3 different mounting options by attaching hinges on the front, back, or on the side of the chassis give access to the case front panel or rear I/O components & ports when mounted on the 19” server rack or make the chassis easy accessible by attaching it to the wall. It is Ultra-Compact 3U Server Chassis with a depth of only 11.8 inches or 303mm. However, even with a smaller size, it has all the benefits of a larger Server case.

TP1833 Chassis can support every ATX motherboard (ATX, microATX and miniATX) as well as ATX PS2 power supply (not included). It has 4 full-height slots on the rear side and will provide 1 x 5.25 and 3 x 3.5" HDD bays. A maximum of 7 spaces for 60mm fans provides excellent airflow (2 fans included). TP1833 is a reliable and stable 3U-high industrial computer chassis. Constructed from a combination of heavy-duty 1.2mm steel and aluminum for handles, it is very rugged. The black color will make it so it easily blends in and makes your equipment look professional. It comes fully assembled so no additional work is needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 4, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 3x 3.5 or 2x 3.5 + 1x 5.25, there are only three total bays not four
reviews.reviewText: In the TP1833 I received there are two 3.5 bays and one 5.25 not four bays in total as stated repeatedly in the description.There is no internal space between the top of the PSU's fan and top cover. Top case cover includes fan holes to vent PSU so if you plan to stack these space has to be left between each server or PSU configured to vent in a different way than normal.Two included fans are fairly quiet.A bit cramped as expected given 12" depth. Not bad, would buy again given not much available under 12" depth. Wish there was a 4U version.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Modular ATX power supplies WONT fit
reviews.reviewText: Sadly I had to return this case. Its built very well and love that its a short depth case. There are a few main reasons I had to return it. 1. Modular power supplies will NOT fit in this case. The hard drive mounting plate is too close to the power supply plugs. This is the main reason I had returned the case, i didn't want to buy a new power supply to make this case work. 2. The hard drive mounting plate is a P.I.T.A to remove. In order to remove or add hard drives, you have to take the power supply out first then remove the hard drive mounting plate. I wasted too much time trying to do this. The hard drive mounting plate will also conflict with many CPU coolers, you will most likely need to buy a low profile CPU cooler. Some other reviews say you can only mount 2 ssd hard drives, this is NOT true. I was able to install 4 Samsung ssd's. Two on the DVD drive side, there are 8 mounting holes on that side, and two on the 3.5" hard drive side. This is a well made case, and if I had a small form factor power supply and a mini-itx motherboard, it would have worked great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 29, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Works for mounting a basic PC in a short depth rack. Everything is tight and I had to make a few cuts to fit a graphics card but this is the best value case I could find.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Solid 3U chasis for its price.
reviews.reviewText: Given the relatively short depth of this it was great for my needs. I was easily able to get a system mounted into it. Have to make sure that your cpu cooling solution and whatever expansion cards you are using are not too tall for the chasis, but for the moderate hardware I used it worked out great.The build quality for the chasis itself isn't the absolute best I've ever worked with and it doesn't have some of the bells and whistles more expensive ones might have, but given its price it is more than reasonable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 2, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Unfortunately for this depth you are extremely limited on options as it is not as widely used,Overall layout is great, the only issue is the dated front panel. Actually like this one more than my supermicro

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 14, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A little out dated for the IO interface
reviews.reviewText: front panel IO with outdated USB 2.0 interface, and the knock out part it for disk drive, I think I would use it for extra IOsThe mount can be put in front and back, which left the back panel to at the front to give more IO, it is a little plus.
